he rest of Canada versus Quebec. Instead, he took Toronto audiences on a global theatre voyage that transformed traditional geopolitical, cultural, and linguistic boundaries and questioned identity. Investigating the relationship between Quebec’s master dramaturge and Toronto, a burgeoning cosmopolitan city determined to be a global cultural capital, Robert Lepage on the Toronto Stage analyzes the success of one of the few Québécois artists to have achieved fame in English Canada.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aTheaterxProduction and directionzOntariozToronto. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Theater / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077359868340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773598683423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773598683/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles